stu_tags: PARTICIPATION MATTERS  RESPECTED  SKIP CLASS? YOU WON\'T PASS.
comments: Professor Davis is extremely serious and structured but she means well. She always explains things if need be and wants to help students as long as they do the work. Her classes are typically boring because the discussions are long but usually very insightful. I would definitely suggest her to any undergraduate social work majors!

tag_professor: Respected (1)  Participation matters (1)  Skip class? You won\'t pass. (1)
comments: The most structured professor I had at Temple. She is no nonsense but she knows her stuff. Class attendance a must. Helpful outside of class if you need assistance.

tag_professor: Respected (1)  Participation matters (1)  Skip class? You won\'t pass. (1)
comments: She\'s relatively young, but very knowledgeable and professional. Grading is fair and she doesn\'t hold you responsible for anything it is she feels was not made clear in class. The only problem I had in this class (Comm in SW practice) was that she would sometimes demand more knowledge of the field itself than a beginning SW student would have.
